    "content": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>Agentic Coding Research Report - 2026-03-02</title>\n    <style>\n        * {\n            margin: 0;\n            padding: 0;\n            box-sizing: border-box;\n        }\n\n        body {\n            font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\n            background-color: #f6f6ef;\n            color: #000000;\n            line-height: 1.5;\n            font-size: 13px;\n        }\n\n        .container {\n            max-width: 1400px;\n            margin: 0 auto;\n            padding: 10px;\n        }\n\n        header {\n            background-color: #ff6600;\n            color: #000;\n            padding: 5px 10px;\n            margin-bottom: 15px;\n            border-radius: 2px;\n        }\n\n        header h1 {\n            font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\n            font-size: 16px;\n            font-weight: bold;\n        }\n\n        header .date {\n            font-size: 12px;\n            margin-top: 2px;\n        }\n\n        .three-column-layout {\n            display: grid;\n            grid-template-columns: 40% 35% 25%;\n            gap: 15px;\n            margin-bottom: 20px;\n        }\n\n        @media (max-width: 1200px) {\n            .three-column-layout {\n                grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;\n            }\n\n            .three-column-layout .technical-insights {\n                grid-column: 1 / -1;\n            }\n        }\n\n        @media (max-width: 768px) {\n            .three-column-layout {\n                grid-template-columns: 1fr;\n            }\n        }\n\n        section {\n            background-color: #ffffff;\n            border: 1px solid #d4d4d4;\n            border-radius: 2px;\n            padding: 10px;\n        }\n\n        section h2 {\n            font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\n            font-size: 14px;\n            font-weight: bold;\n            margin-bottom: 12px;\n            padding-bottom: 8px;\n            border-bottom: 1px solid #ff6600;\n            color: #000;\n        }\n\n        .item {\n            margin-bottom: 15px;\n            padding-bottom: 12px;\n            border-bottom: 1px solid #eeeeee;\n        }\n\n        .item:last-child {\n            margin-bottom: 0;\n            padding-bottom: 0;\n            border-bottom: none;\n        }\n\n        .item-title {\n            font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\n            font-size: 13px;\n            font-weight: normal;\n            margin-bottom: 5px;\n        }\n\n        .item-title a {\n            color: #000;\n            text-decoration: none;\n        }\n\n        .item-title a:visited {\n            color: #828282;\n        }\n\n        .item-title a:hover {\n            text-decoration: underline;\n        }\n\n        .item-title .source-arrow {\n            color: #ff6600;\n            margin-right: 4px;\n            font-weight: bold;\n        }\n\n        .description {\n            color: #828282;\n            font-size: 12px;\n            line-height: 1.4;\n            margin-bottom: 6px;\n        }\n\n        .meta {\n            font-size: 11px;\n            color: #828282;\n        }\n\n        .meta .category {\n            display: inline-block;\n            background-color: #f6f6ef;\n            padding: 2px 6px;\n            border-radius: 2px;\n            margin-right: 5px;\n            font-family: Monaco, Consolas, monospace;\n        }\n\n        .meta .release-date {\n            color: #828282;\n        }\n\n        .quote {\n            background-color: #f6f6ef;\n            border-left: 2px solid #ff6600;\n            padding: 6px 10px;\n            margin-top: 8px;\n            font-style: italic;\n            font-size: 11px;\n            color: #555;\n        }\n\n        .author {\n            font-size: 11px;\n            color: #828282;\n            margin-top: 4px;\n        }\n\n        .author a {\n            color: #828282;\n            text-decoration: none;\n        }\n\n        .author a:hover {\n            text-decoration: underline;\n        }\n\n        .topics {\n            margin-top: 6px;\n        }\n\n        .topic {\n            display: inline-block;\n            font-size: 10px;\n            color: #828282;\n            margin-right: 8px;\n            font-family: Monaco, Consolas, monospace;\n        }\n\n        .empty-section {\n            color: #828282;\n            font-style: italic;\n            text-align: center;\n            padding: 20px;\n        }\n\n        .insight-type {\n            display: inline-block;\n            font-size: 10px;\n            padding: 2px 6px;\n            border-radius: 2px;\n            margin-bottom: 5px;\n            font-weight: bold;\n            text-transform: uppercase;\n        }\n\n        .insight-type.technical {\n            background-color: #e8f4f8;\n            color: #2c5282;\n        }\n\n        .insight-type.opinion {\n            background-color: #fef5e7;\n            color: #9c7c2c;\n        }\n\n        .insight-type.tutorial {\n            background-color: #e8f5e8;\n            color: #2c6e2c;\n        }\n\n        .insight-type.discussion {\n            background-color: #f3e8f8;\n            color: #6b2c6e;\n        }\n\n        footer {\n            text-align: center;\n            padding: 15px 10px;\n            color: #828282;\n            font-size: 11px;\n            border-top: 1px solid #d4d4d4;\n            margin-top: 20px;\n        }\n\n        footer a {\n            color: #828282;\n            text-decoration: none;\n        }\n\n        footer a:hover {\n            text-decoration: underline;\n        }\n\n        @media print {\n            body {\n                background-color: #ffffff;\n            }\n\n            section {\n                border: none;\n                page-break-inside: avoid;\n            }\n\n            .three-column-layout {\n                display: block;\n            }\n\n            section {\n                margin-bottom: 20px;\n                page-break-before: always;\n            }\n\n            section:first-of-type {\n                page-break-before: avoid;\n            }\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <div class=\"container\">\n        <header>\n            <h1>Agentic Coding Research Report</h1>\n            <div class=\"date\">2026-03-02</div>\n        </header>\n\n        <main class=\"three-column-layout\">\n            <!-- New Products Section (40%) -->\n            <section class=\"new-products\">\n                <h2>New Products</h2>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <span class=\"source-arrow\">▸</span>\n                        <a href=\"https://github.com/openclaw\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">GLM-5 with OpenClaw</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"description\">Open-source AI coding agent framework with 161K+ GitHub stars. Features built-in LanceDB memory plugin for persistent workspace memory, autonomous coding capabilities, and Terminal Bench 2.0 score of 56.2 (open-source SOTA).</div>\n                    <div class=\"meta\">\n                        <span class=\"category\">Open-source coding agent</span>\n                        <span class=\"release-date\">Released: 2026-02-27</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"quote\">\"Peter (OpenClaw creator) predicts 2026 will see 'complete explosion' of Agentic Coding. Completed over 90,000 GitHub commits across 120+ projects using AI Agent tools\"</div>\n                    <div class=\"meta\">\n                        <span class=\"release-date\">Sources: GitHub, Tech blogs</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <span class=\"source-arrow\">▸</span>\n                        <a href=\"https://opencode.ai\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">OpenCode AI</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"description\">Terminal-based AI coding agent built specifically for the CLI with TUI interface. Supports installation via npm, brew, and curl. Works with multiple LLMs including Claude, OpenAI, Google Gemini, and local models.</div>\n                    <div class=\"meta\">\n                        <span class=\"category\">AI coding CLI</span>\n                        <span class=\"release-date\">Released: 2026-02-26</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"meta\">\n                        <span class=\"release-date\">Sources: Product Hunt, GitHub</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <span class=\"source-arrow\">▸</span>\n                        <a href=\"https://figr.ai\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Figr</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"description\">AI product assistant for product managers. Chrome extension that real-time parses applications, imports Figma designs, adds documentation and analytics, creates user flows, UX evaluations, and A/B test variants based on 200,000+ UX patterns.</div>\n                    <div class=\"meta\">\n                        <span class=\"category\">Workflow agent</span>\n                        <span class=\"release-date\">Released: 2026-02-18</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"meta\">\n                        <span class=\"release-date\">Sources: Product Hunt</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <span class=\"source-arrow\">▸</span>\n                        <a href=\"https://base44.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Base44</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"description\">Complete backend service for building AI agent applications. Optimized for Claude Code and Cursor. Deploy full-stack applications with a single command. Tested across millions of real-world applications.</div>\n                    <div class=\"meta\">\n                        <span class=\"category\">Workflow agent</span>\n                        <span class=\"release-date\">Released: 2026-02-17</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"meta\">\n                        <span class=\"release-date\">Sources: Product Hunt</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <span class=\"source-arrow\">▸</span>\n                        <a href=\"https://qwen-ai.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Qwen Coder</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"description\">Autonomous coding agent from Alibaba's Qwen team. Part of Qwen Agent framework, optimized for coding tasks including writing, debugging, and fixing code. Released as part of Qwen 3.5 framework.</div>\n                    <div class=\"meta\">\n                        <span class=\"category\">AI coding agent</span>\n                        <span class=\"release-date\">Released: 2026-02-16</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"meta\">\n                        <span class=\"release-date\">Sources: GitHub, Product announcements</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </section>\n\n            <!-- Whitelist Updates Section (35%) -->\n            <section class=\"whitelist-updates\">\n                <h2>Whitelist Updates</h2>\n                <div class=\"empty-section\">No updates for this period</div>\n            </section>\n\n            <!-- Technical Insights Section (25%) -->\n            <section class=\"technical-insights\">\n                <h2>Technical Insights</h2>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <span class=\"insight-type technical\">Technical</span>\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <span class=\"source-arrow\">▸</span>\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/27/ai-agent-coding-skeptic/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">An AI agent coding skeptic tries AI agent coding, in excessive detail</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"description\">Max Woolf's journey from skepticism to enthusiasm about AI coding agents. Key insight: \"Opus 4.5 (and the models that came after it) are an order of magnitude better than coding LLMs released just months before it\"</div>\n                    <div class=\"author\">By <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Max Woolf (covered by Simon Willison)</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"topics\">\n                        <span class=\"topic\">AI coding agents</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic\">Rust</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic\">scikit-learn</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <span class=\"insight-type technical\">Technical</span>\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <span class=\"source-arrow\">▸</span>\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/27/claude-max-open-source/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Free Claude Max for (large project) open source maintainers</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"description\">Anthropic now offers their $200/month Claude Max 20x plan for free to open source maintainers for six months. Criteria: primary maintainer of public repo with 5,000+ GitHub stars OR 1M+ monthly NPM downloads.</div>\n                    <div class=\"author\">By <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Simon Willison</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"topics\">\n                        <span class=\"topic\">Claude</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic\">open source</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic\">developer tools</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <span class=\"insight-type technical\">Technical</span>\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <span class=\"source-arrow\">▸</span>\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/27/unicode-explorer/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Unicode Explorer using binary search over fetch() HTTP range requests</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"description\">Simon built a prototype tool from his phone demonstrating HTTP range requests and binary search. Key technical insight: Range request tricks aren't compatible with HTTP compression due to byte offset calculations.</div>\n                    <div class=\"author\">By <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Simon Willison</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"topics\">\n                        <span class=\"topic\">HTTP</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic\">binary search</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic\">AI-assisted programming</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <span class=\"insight-type tutorial\">Tutorial</span>\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <span class=\"source-arrow\">▸</span>\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/26/agentic-hoard/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Agentic Engineering Patterns: Hoard things you know how to do</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"description\">A key pattern for working productively with coding agents: understanding what's possible and having rough ideas of how to accomplish things. The skill is knowing what questions to ask.</div>\n                    <div class=\"author\">By <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Simon Willison</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"topics\">\n                        <span class=\"topic\">agentic engineering</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic\">AI coding patterns</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <span class=\"insight-type technical\">Technical</span>\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <span class=\"source-arrow\">▸</span>\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/26/google-api-keys/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Google API Keys Weren't Secrets. But then Gemini Changed the Rules.</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"description\">Critical security issue: Google Maps API keys can access Gemini API endpoints when Gemini is enabled on the same project. Truffle Security found 2,863 API keys that could access Gemini.</div>\n                    <div class=\"author\">By <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Simon Willison</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"topics\">\n                        <span class=\"topic\">security</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic\">Google</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic\">API keys</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <span class=\"insight-type opinion\">Opinion</span>\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <span class=\"source-arrow\">▸</span>\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/26/karpathy-december/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Coding agents didn't work before December, basically work since - Andrej Karpathy</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"description\">\"Coding agents basically didn't work before December and basically work since - the models have significantly higher quality, long-term coherence and tenacity.\" - Andrej Karpathy on the December 2025 inflection point.</div>\n                    <div class=\"author\">By <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Andrej Karpathy (quoted by Simon Willison)</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"topics\">\n                        <span class=\"topic\">AI coding agents</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic\">LLM improvement</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <span class=\"insight-type technical\">Technical</span>\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <span class=\"source-arrow\">▸</span>\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/25/claude-remote-control/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Claude Code Remote Control</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"description\">New Claude Code feature: run 'remote control' session on computer and use Claude Code for web interfaces to send prompts. Current limitations: only one session at a time, doesn't support --dangerously-skip-permissions flag.</div>\n                    <div class=\"author\">By <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Simon Willison</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"topics\">\n                        <span class=\"topic\">Claude Code</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic\">remote control</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic\">AI agents</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <span class=\"insight-type opinion\">Opinion</span>\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <span class=\"source-arrow\">▸</span>\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/25/vibe-coded-present/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">I vibe coded my dream macOS presentation app</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"description\">Simon vibe coded a custom macOS presentation app the night before his talk at Social Science FOO Camp. Talk title: \"The State of LLMs, February 2026 edition\" with subtitle \"It's all changed since November!\"</div>\n                    <div class=\"author\">By <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Simon Willison</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"topics\">\n                        <span class=\"topic\">vibe coding</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic\">macOS</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic\">SwiftUI</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <span class=\"insight-type tutorial\">Tutorial</span>\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <span class=\"source-arrow\">▸</span>\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/25/linear-walkthroughs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Agentic Engineering Patterns: Linear walkthroughs</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"description\">Pattern for using coding agents to get structured walkthroughs of codebases - whether existing code you're learning, your own forgotten code, or vibe-coded code you need to understand.</div>\n                    <div class=\"author\">By <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Simon Willison</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"topics\">\n                        <span class=\"topic\">agentic engineering</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic\">code understanding</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <span class=\"insight-type technical\">Technical</span>\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <span class=\"source-arrow\">▸</span>\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/24/ladybird-rust-ai/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Ladybird adopts Rust, with help from AI</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"description\">Andreas Kling reports using Claude Code and Codex to port Ladybird's JavaScript engine (LibJS) from C++ to Rust. Result: 25,000 lines of Rust in ~2 weeks with zero regressions. Success enabled by test262 conformance testing suite.</div>\n                    <div class=\"author\">By <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Andreas Kling (covered by Simon Willison)</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"topics\">\n                        <span class=\"topic\">Rust</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic\">browsers</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic\">Ladybird</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <span class=\"insight-type opinion\">Opinion</span>\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <span class=\"source-arrow\">▸</span>\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/23/writing-code-is-cheap/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Agentic Engineering Patterns: Writing code is cheap now</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"description\">The biggest challenge in adopting agentic engineering: getting comfortable with the fact that writing code is cheap now. With AI, producing hundreds of lines of clean, tested code is suddenly trivial. This requires rethinking everything from how we evaluate features to how we approach refactoring.</div>\n                    <div class=\"author\">By <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Simon Willison</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"topics\">\n                        <span class=\"topic\">agentic engineering</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic\">AI economics</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <span class=\"insight-type discussion\">Discussion</span>\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <span class=\"source-arrow\">▸</span>\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/25/tldraw-tests/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">tldraw considers moving tests to closed source repo (later revealed as joke)</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"description\">tldraw filed an issue about moving their test suite to private repo, in response to Cloudflare porting Next.js to Vite in a week using AI. The concern: comprehensive test suites are enough to build completely fresh implementations of open source libraries from scratch. Update: The issue was a joke.</div>\n                    <div class=\"author\">By <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Simon Willison</a></div>\n                    <div class=\"topics\">\n                        <span class=\"topic\">open source</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic\">AI ethics</span>\n                        <span class=\"topic\">test suites</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </section>\n        </main>\n\n        <footer>\n            <p>Agentic Coding Research Report | <a href=\"#\">Archives</a> | <a href=\"#\">About</a> | <a href=\"#\">Subscribe</a></p>\n            <p style=\"margin-top: 5px;\">Generated with research data from the agentic coding ecosystem</p>\n        </footer>\n    </div>\n</body>\n</html>",
